[{"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Konami just stealth launched a Silent Hill game", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T23:01:16+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Silent Hill 2 featuring Pyramid Head standing in a door frame.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/T4_fRm944rWz5M7wHHiNNEVBctU=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101784/SH2_8.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Konami</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SJaFeP\"><em>Silent Hill,</em> the town in desperate need of a city council or something, showed up during PlayStation\u2019s State of Play in a big way with two new trailers and a stealth drop of a new, free-to-play game.</p>\n<p id=\"BY2qjD\">The first game was the debut of <em>Silent Hill: The Short Message</em>, an all-new entry in the <em>Silent Hill</em> franchise. <a href=\"https://blog.playstation.com/2024/01/31/silent-hill-the-short-message-now-available-free-on-ps5-new-silent-hill-2-remake-trailer-revealed/\">According to PlayStation\u2019s blog</a>, <em>The Short Message</em> is a short, experimental, free-to-play game meant to introduce newcomers to t", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057338/silent-hill-2-trailer-short-message-state-of-play", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Death Stranding 2\u2019s new trailer is delightfully disturbing", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T22:46:21+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of Norman Reedus in Death Stranding 2.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/H8BSfwc5b3MFIGpTr-m1okukUO4=/300x0:1920x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101733/ds2_tga2022_screenshot005_2k.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Kojima Productions</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"GHoIDI\">The sequel to <em>Death Stranding</em> is shaping up to be just as strange <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/11/1/20941606/death-stranding-review-ps4-hideo-kojima\">as the original</a>. At its State of Play showcase today, Sony showed off a new trailer for the game that... starts out with a particularly disturbing bit of surgery. The lengthy clip features a whole bunch of new locations outside of the US, as well as the return of a villain who has been given a Joker-esque makeover. And yes, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/11/8/20953147/death-stranding-ps4-bb-baby-hideo-kojima\">the baby makes an appearance</a> \u2014 along with", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24055773/death-stranding-2-ps5-trailer-2025", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Apple\u2019s Vision Pro battery pack is hiding the final boss of Lightning cables", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T22:33:29+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of the connector from the Vision Pro battery. It looks like a Lightning connector, only wider and with four extra pins.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xDp4UE0w4-BfXXAAhkxEZYSfDE8=/0x1380:3024x3396/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101700/IMG_2054.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Vision Pro\u2019s not-a-Lightning-connector connector.</em> | Image: Nilay Patel / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3rg28O\">Ray Wong of <em>Inverse</em> <a href=\"https://x.com/raywongy/status/1752787114071298255?s=20\">discovered a hidden joy today</a>: The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23689334/apple-mixed-reality-headset-augmented-virtual-reality-ar-vr-rumors-specs-features\">Apple Vision Pro</a> power cable connects to the battery with what may well be Lightning\u2019s final form. Using a SIM removal tool, he pushed into a small hole in the silver external battery pack of the Vision Pro next to the cable, and...</p>\n<p id=\"ure", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057392/apple-vision-pro-battery-lightning-cable", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Microsoft LASERs away LLM inaccuracies", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T21:46:36+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Microsoft logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tqactvL0Tr5oK1sHiq760YMlMPU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101579/STK095_Microsoft_04.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wODsAD\">During the January <a href=\"https://click.linksynergy.com/deeplink?id=nOD%2FrLJHOac&amp;mid=24542&amp;u1=verge&amp;murl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fresearch%2Fquarterly-brief%2Fjan-2024-brief%2Farticles%2Fimproving-reasoning-in-language-models-with-laser-layer-selective-rank-reduction%2F\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Microsoft Research Forum</a>, Dipendra Misra, a senior researcher at Microsoft Research Lab NYC and AI Frontiers, explained how Layer-Selective Rank Reduction (or LASER) can make large language models more accurate. </p>\n<p id=\"jmGntr\">With LASER, researchers can \u201cintervene\u201d and replace one weight matrix with an approximate smaller o", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057362/microsoft-llm-accuracy-laser-research-ai", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "All the news from PlayStation\u2019s 2024 State of Play", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T21:22:22+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of the PlaySation \u201cPS\u201d logo overlayed on swooping blue and teal colors\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/oW9mjXWV4Z7Axeq1Crxth4VhXb8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101465/acastro_STK097_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>During the roughly 40-minute presentation, expect to hear new info on Rise of the Ronin, Death Stranding, Sonic Generations, Judas, and more.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24055776/playstation-state-of-play-january-2024-sony\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24055776/playstation-state-of-play-january-2024-sony", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Philips stops selling sleep apnea machines in US following mass recalls", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T20:34:26+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing a Philips DreamStation machine\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OIG9mbmBeHwb4C6vCa3q1rzoHVU=/0x23:1436x980/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101377/philips_sleep_apnea_machine.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Philips</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hnzEiQ\">Philips is halting sales of its recalled sleep apnea machines in the US after finding they were pumping foam particles into users\u2019 airways. In <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.philips.com%2Fa-w%2Fabout%2Fnews%2Farchive%2Fcorpcomms%2Fnews%2Fpress%2F2024%2Fphilips-fourth-quarter-results-2023.html&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F1%2F31%2F24056939%2Fphilips-sleep-apnea-machines-recalls\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">its earnings report</a> on Monday, the company says it will not sell new CPAP or BiPAP devices in the US until it meets th", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056939/philips-sleep-apnea-machines-recalls", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Amazon left Roomba with a huge mess to clean up", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T20:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3Aa2whrs4OSl-Zp8nnpyWsko5IE=/0x0:5760x3840/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101261/8A0A0511.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The newest Roomba vacuum \u2014 the Combo j9 Plus \u2014 faces stiff competition.</em> | Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>By abandoning its deal to buy iRobot, Amazon has left the robot vacuum maker stuck under the couch.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057077/irobot-amazon-deal-collapse-roomba-uncertain-future\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057077/irobot-amazon-deal-collapse-roomba-uncertain-future", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "The creators of Twitterrific are making an app to read (almost) anything on the web", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T19:56:14+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qLELWzyi2EvN9Kc3t_nTUwH6CP4=/116x0:1898x1188/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101247/Screen_Shot_2024_01_31_at_11.01.59_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Iconfactory</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"EF3769\">After nearly 16 years in operation, Twitterrific was abruptly deactivated last year during Twitter\u2019s<strong> </strong>unceremonious purging of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/1/22/23564460/twitter-third-party-apps-history-contributions\">third-party apps</a>. Now, the app\u2019s developer Iconfactory is <a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/iconfactory/project-tapestry\">raising funds on Kickstarter</a> to create Project Tapestry<strong>, </strong>a new internet reader for the publicly accessible web. The iOS app will serve as a \u201cuniversal, chronological timeline,\u201d pulling from federated social media networks like Mastodon and Bluesky, as well as Tumblr, Micro.blog, and any RSS ", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057231/iconfactory-kickstarter-internet-reader-project-tapestry-twitterrific", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Microsoft\u2019s new OneDrive design starts rolling out for consumers", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T19:38:37+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the new OneDrive UI\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ddqF1UH2j2OBSc8mzV1G8j3etzU=/0x0:1320x880/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101215/onedrive3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VMNKVc\">Microsoft is starting to roll out a new design for its OneDrive cloud storage service for consumers. The software maker first unveiled a Fluent design refresh for OneDrive last year, and it will be available to all OneDrive personal users by the end of February.</p>\n<p id=\"3l62XX\">\u201cIt\u2019s both a visual and functional upgrade designed to help you get to your files quickly and keep your content organized in multiple ways,\u201d <a href=\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-onedrive-blog/new-year-new-look-for-onedrive-for-personal-use/ba-p/4039162\">says Miceile Barrett</a>, a Microsoft product manager. \u201cThe improved visual design reduces clutter and distractions, allowing you", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057235/microsoft-new-onedrive-design-rolling-out-consumers", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Crypto mines will have to start reporting their energy use in the US", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T19:30:56+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Racks of Bitcoin mining machines with wires hanging from them.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YvlJlVKV8UtBPJerSfhkyq5CX2c=/0x3:7360x4910/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101179/1235927106.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Bitcoin mining machines in a warehouse at the Whinstone US Bitcoin mining facility in Rockdale, Texas, on October 10, 2021.&nbsp;</em> | Photo by MARK FELIX/AFP /AFP via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"0oMqlI\">The US Department of Energy (DOE) will begin collecting data on crypto mines\u2019 electricity use, following criticism from environmental advocates over how energy-hungry those operations are. </p>\n<p id=\"bnZe9c\">\u201cWe will specifically focus on how the energy demand for cryptocurrency mining is evolving, identify geographic areas of high growth, and quantify the sources of electricity used to meet cryptocurrency mining demand,\u201d Joe DeCarolis, administrator of the Energy Information Admin", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057176/crypto-bitcoin-mining-survey-us-energy-information-administration", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "JBL\u2019s retro-inspired Authentics speakers are on sale for nearly 25 percent off", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T19:09:02+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"JBL Authentics 200 sits on a table in a living room.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GmA1xThdlMYmcGQm8DioLOk8tJo=/0x0:6240x4160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101113/DSCF0306.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>You can make Alexa and Google Assistant fight for your love with JBL\u2019s retro-styled speakers.</em> | Photo by Jon Porter / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"f76M6j\">I know that someone, somewhere, shares my thinking that the virtual assistants we\u2019ve grown fond of are mortal enemies somewhere in a digital parallel universe. But <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/8/31/23853487/jbl-authentics-200-300-500-hands-on-alexa-google-assistant-smart-speaker\">JBL\u2019s new line of Authentics speakers</a> has warped everything I thought I knew about the ancient rivalry, allowing you to call on either assistant without toggling a setting.</p>\n<p id=\"hS4AYR\">Right now, you can pay as little as $274.95 ($75 off) for the", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24055594/jbl-authentics-200-300-500-opal-tadpole-webcam-sony-wh-1000xm5-headphones-deal-sale", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Microsoft Teams, Word, Excel, and more are coming to Apple\u2019s Vision Pro at launch", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T18:56:53+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Microsoft Teams in Apple Vision Pro\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/swYDmp9OgItWoUOXHJjd4JDubmI=/111x0:1319x805/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73101050/Apple_Vision_Pro.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"pdqqSl\">Microsoft is launching a suite of its Microsoft 365 apps on Apple\u2019s Vision Pro headset later this week. Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, OneNote, Loop, and Microsoft Teams <a href=\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-blog/announcing-microsoft-365-apps-now-available-on-apple-vision-pro/ba-p/4042505\">will all be available</a> in the App Store for Apple Vision Pro on February 2nd \u2014 the same day Apple\u2019s new headset is available in stores.</p>\n<p id=\"3ylaXg\">Apple Vision Pro owners will also be able to access an AI-powered version of Copilot while using the headset, including the ability to create drafts, summarize documents, and generate PowerPo", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057122/microsoft-apple-vision-pro-office-apps-microsoft-365", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Palworld isn\u2019t slowing down, hits 19 million players across Steam and Xbox", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T18:37:38+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of the video game Palworld.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gwQuqqfIEqhcRnbQCgY2WM2j230=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100984/ss_22508261f9d361c8dda95e8adc54292ad085e8e1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Pocketpair</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SCEBuz\">Surprise <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/22/24047087/palworld-early-access-steam-xbox-gamepass\">viral gaming hit <em>Palworld</em></a> continues to reach new player milestones. Today, developer Pocketpair announced that the game has <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Palworld_EN/status/1752753619429163190\">sold 12 million copies on Steam</a> and reached 7 million players on Xbox. The Xbox number includes both sales and those who played via Game Pass, but the breakdown between the two isn\u2019t clear.</p>\n<p id=\"yANCqt\"><a href=\"https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2024/01/31/palworld-biggest-3rd-party-game-pass-launch-ever/\">According to Microso", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24057131/palworld-steam-xbox-game-pass-sales", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Shopify\u2019s \u2018Magic\u2019 AI image editor can make any product pics look professional", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T18:22:29+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot of Shopify\u2019s image editor generating new backgrounds for a shiny winter jacket based on a text prompt.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4JBHgjTKqi-Z3Q_nBfYkey_kngk=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100914/videoframe_1049267.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Shopify Magic Media Editor.</em> | Image: Shopify</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"DOyUvM\">The Shopify Magic suite of generative AI tools that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23753963/google-seo-shopify-small-business-ai\">launched in April last year</a> is adding a media editor that brings generative image fill to its platform and conversational search powered by AI. Merchants can prompt the image editor to change photo backgrounds without Photoshop experience to match whatever theme they have in mind. </p>\n<p id=\"D70YOC\">Shopify\u2019s AI editor can also suggest backgrounds and styles that match existing product images in the merchant\u2019s library", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24056980/shopify-generative-ai-image-editing-search", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "FTX says it will pay back customers", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T17:44:59+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"FTX logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/E-6TlhwsGhQ9gp_UIC6xmMEPn3Q=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100751/STK136_K_Radtke_FTX_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9rpskn\">FTX says it will repay investors after the cryptocurrency exchange\u2019s collapse led to the loss of billions of dollars. During <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jHbFL9M7Cgo\">a court hearing</a> on Wednesday, FTX lawyer Andrew Dietderich said the company expects to \u201chave sufficient funds to pay all allowed customer and creditor claims in full.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"YwNFQ3\">The company will recompense customers based on the price of the cryptocurrency they purchased as of November 2022 \u2014 when the exchange filed for bankruptcy. There are still some challenges associated with getting the lost funds back to customers, though, as Dietderich notes the company will need to comb through all the cl", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056991/ftx-repay-customers-bankruptcy", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "A tough break for rugged phone fans as key manufacturer shuts down", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T17:40:33+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Someone holding a Cat S75 smartphone in a rocky, outdoor environment.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gdUvG45H4b8_0xBVTWZTTinqd9o=/0x10:1920x1290/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100733/CAT_S75_rugged_phone.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>There\u2019s no word yet on how Bullitt-produced phones like the Cat S75 (pictured) will be affected.</em> | Image: Cat</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"B40Uf2\">Bullitt Group, the UK-based smartphone manufacturer behind the rugged handsets of Cat, Land Rover, and Motorola, has seemingly shut down. On Monday, <a href=\"https://www.mobileworldlive.com/devices/bullitt-group-hits-skids-with-restructure/\"><em>Mobile World Live</em> spotted several</a> Bullitt Group employees on LinkedIn saying that the company <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7157729389646942208/\">folded on January 26th</a> after a \u201c<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:715771", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056970/bullitt-group-rugged-smartphones-cat-motorola-folded-insolvency", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "The Pixel 8 is getting Google\u2019s new AI search feature today", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T17:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration showing how Google\u2019s Circle to Search feature works, with a finger circling a pair of glasses, and a search bar superimposed over the image.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0IiXYSXOoDChEk07vWCkM0XPOMM=/301x0:1300x666/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100607/SGE_Jan_2024_Circle_to_Search__1_.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>\u2018Circle to Search\u2019 comes to Pixel 8 and 8 Pro phones.</em> | Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rWKmDa\">Google is <a href=\"https://blog.google/products/search/how-to-use-circle-to-search-google/\">rolling out</a> its \u201cCircle to Search\u201d feature to Pixel 8 phones today, bringing new ideas about how to gather information on the internet using AI. The feature, which is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/17/24040715/samsung-galaxy-s24-ultra-specs-price-ai\">also available</a> on Samsung Galaxy S24 phones, builds on Google\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/11/23063809", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056890/circle-to-search-google-pixel-8-pro-update", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "The best wireless earbuds to buy right now", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T15:30:55+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Sony\u2019s WF-1000XM5 earbuds.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/e6t1Ea8VCnt9pPlNtEqC2_bCfCc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/67005648/DSCF2232.22.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The best from Apple, Bose, Samsung, Sony, Beats, Google, and more.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21309820/best-wireless-earbuds\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/21309820/best-wireless-earbuds", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Samsung\u2019s Galaxy S24 Ultra really is scratch resistant", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T15:09:36+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra shown in-hand with Google\u2019s Circle to Search results shown on-screen.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BhJe-QooPeS_fFhhpFPEPf19HPQ=/0x0:2000x1333/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100198/DSC06312_processed.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wA0kxm\">One of the most impressive parts of Samsung\u2019s new Galaxy S24 Ultra is the anti-glare display, which is made of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/17/24041838/samsung-galaxy-s24-ultra-scratch-resistance-corning-gorilla-armor\">Corning Gorilla Armor glass</a> that <a href=\"https://news.samsung.com/global/samsung-galaxy-s24-ultra-creates-new-standards-of-durability-and-visual-clarity-with-corning-gorilla-armor\">Samsung touts</a> as its \u201cmost scratch-resistant yet.\u201d Although it\u2019s easy to dismiss that claim as marketing speak, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nyxcO2vdcCg&amp;t=308s\"", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056747/samsung-s24-ultra-scratch-resistant-display-durability-test", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Epic preps its challenge to Apple\u2019s \u2018bad-faith\u2019 outside payments changes", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T15:08:31+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Image of the Apple logo surrounded by gray, pink, and green outlines\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Zndz86NkMj5B5eG3PjuVmXbeCCA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100195/VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_5_apple.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UQewdF\">Epic is not pleased with how Apple has responded to court orders. It thinks Apple\u2019s new 27 percent tax on developers that link to non-Apple payment methods defies a court order to let developers provide those links and yesterday notified the court that it plans to lay out exactly how. </p>\n<p id=\"24FLkT\">To refresh, District Court Judge Yvonne Gonzalez Rogers <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/9/12/22667694/epic-v-apple-trial-fortnite-judge-yvonne-gonzalez-rogers-final-ruling-injunction-breakdown\">ordered Apple</a> in 2021 to let developers link to outside payment methods, and it <a href=\"https://www", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056751/epic-notice-apple-app-store-outside-payments-link-27-percent", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "TikTok is set to lose some major musical artists over AI and pay dispute", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T14:49:21+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A brain with wires over a field of music notes\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1dUt__hNXy4QVpXLufznol5s5pU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100109/acastro_190416_1777_music_ai_0001.0.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The current licensing agreement between TikTok and UMG is set to expire on January 31st.</em> | Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"00VXz0\">The music catalogs of Taylor Swift, Drake, Harry Styles, and many other <a href=\"https://www.umusicpub.com/hr/Artists.aspx\">artists represented by Universal Music Group</a> (UMG) are expected to be pulled from TikTok following accusations that the video platform attempted to \u201cbully\u201d and \u201cintimidate\u201d the record label into accepting a subpar licensing deal. The current licensing agreement between TikTok and UMG is set to lapse today, January 31st, <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/technology/universal-musics-licensing-agre", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056727/universal-music-group-umg-tiktok-music-removal-ai-pay-negotiations", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "All the news from Congress\u2019 Big Tech child safety hearing", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T14:45:00+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The US Capitol building during daytime\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fw0Cj3jnuv7QX5zR9nLautLd_08=/194x0:1766x1048/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100087/29947847713_6c70d75f1d_k.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/uscapitol/29947847713/in/album-72157627522484962/\" target=\"_blank\">US Capitol / Flickr</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>The CEOs of five major tech companies will make a case for why their platforms are safe for kids.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056136/congress-child-safety-hearing-kosa-meta-x-discord-snap-tiktok\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056136/congress-child-safety-hearing-kosa-meta-x-discord-snap-tiktok", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "How to watch today\u2019s PlayStation State of Play showcase", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T14:30:00+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Sony\u2019s PS5 console.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2FldZs978ERJt7Ujn6lNmIaVoIQ=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73100033/vpavic_4278_20201030_0292.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"L2Xm6H\">Sony is ending the first month of the year with a big ol\u2019 livestream full of gaming news. The next <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/29/24054261/playstation-state-of-play-february-2024-date-stream\">PlayStation State of Play</a> kicks off this afternoon, and the company is promising 40 minutes that will cover quite a few video games \u2014 more than 15, in fact.</p>\n<p id=\"V7cvJ6\">Only two titles have been confirmed, with Team Ninja\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/games/2023/12/7/23993019/rise-of-the-ronin-is-coming-out-in-march\"><em>Rise of the Ronin</em></a> and the anime-style adventure game <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ayek3ZzWb1E&amp;vl=e", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24055732/playstation-state-of-play-time-date-live-stream", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Nvidia RTX 4080 Super review: $999 is the main feature", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T14:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<p>Nvidia\u2019s final RTX 40-series Super card offers a small performance bump but an intriguing price drop.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24055394/nvidia-rtx-4080-super-review-gpu-graphics-card-benchmark-test\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24055394/nvidia-rtx-4080-super-review-gpu-graphics-card-benchmark-test", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "The Vision Pro is a computer for the age of walled gardens", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T13:30:00+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1SU-UGuTA1choWscAgwwQ1R_piA=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73099887/246965_vision_pro_VPavic_0265.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gA5Et5\">The Vision Pro, Apple\u2019s new \u201cspatial computing\u201d headset, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24054862/apple-vision-pro-review-vr-ar-headset-features-price\">comes with a lot of limits</a>. It\u2019s a technically impressive $3,499 device that\u2019s straining against the basic capabilities of screens, cameras, eye tracking, and sheer component weight. Yet as I\u2019ve watched the Vision Pro go from announcement to release, it\u2019s also seemed held back by something that has little to do with hardware. Apple is trying to create the computer of the future, but it\u2019s doing so under the tech company mindset of the present: one obsessed with consolidation, closed ecosystems, and treating platforms as ", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24055677/apple-vision-pro-epic-netflix-app-ecosystem-monopoly", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "How to watch Linda Yaccarino, Mark Zuckerberg, and other tech CEOs testify in Congress", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T13:09:24+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Mark Zuckerberg testifies in front of a microphone in a hearing in Congress\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PZXyY7vDV7Ui1Y8JKYcJQd9qVoY=/0x0:6720x4480/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73099864/1177753363.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>It\u2019s not Zuckerberg\u2019s first time in front of Congress. | Photo by Aurora Samperio/NurPhoto via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xiIJGl\">Today, the US Senate Judiciary Committee will hear testimony from five CEOs of major tech companies: Linda Yaccarino of X, Shou Zi Chew of TikTok, Evan Spiegel of Snap, Mark Zuckerberg of Meta, and Jason Citron of Discord. The executives will answer questions on the topic of \u201cBig Tech and the online child sexual exploitation crisis,\u201d an ongoing issue for a Congress that\u2019s introduced numerous child safety bills in recent years.</p>\n<p id=\"3xTgoB\">The hearing has been months in the making and apparently involved a little strong-arming from Congress,", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24049456/yaccarino-zuckerberg-tiktok-x-meta-senate-judiciary-hearing-live-stream-how-to-watch", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "The Indiglo button let there be light", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T12:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "user": null, "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EQMQdLTPelmiUrovWft5nSfgic4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73099723/236748_BOTM_Timex_Indiglo_watch_AKrales_0121.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Indiglo button on a modern Timex Weekender.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap\" id=\"bXaBrJ\">Long before the self-lit pixels of OLED phones illuminated our lives, there was a time many portable gadgets didn\u2019t shine <em>at all</em>. Remember when the display of practically every Nintendo Game Boy was designed to be viewed by sunlight? Remember when it was tough to tell time with your average wristwatch after dark?</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><div id=\"3eEZJu\"><div></div></div></div>\n<p id=\"XMl6Gf\">But in 1992, Timex popularized a push-button technology that could bathe any small display in a soothing, sea-green glow. And even though the actual <em>", "permanent": false, "language": "en", "source_obj__id": 61, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24051162/indiglo-button-of-the-month", "bookmarked": false, "vote": 0}, {"thumbnail": null, "tags": [], "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Lawmakers propose anti-nonconsensual AI porn bill after Taylor Swift controversy", "page_rating_contents": 0, "age": null, "date_published": "2024-01-31T02:44:20+00:00", "page_rating_votes": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.co